cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of classifying objects using depth information captured by robots. It proposes a deep network architecture that learns how to map depth data to three channel images, which is a problem related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of pre-trained deep architectures, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with the application of this approach to robotics (cs.RO).
